HEADWORD: Unglaze
<hw>Un*glaze"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>glaze</ets>.]</ety> <def>To strip of glass; to
remove the glazing, or glass, from, as a window.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

